    "actions_taken": [
      "ROV diagnostic testing initiated on 27 June 2020",
      "Integrity issue confirmed on 29 June 2020",
      "Further diagnostic testing performed on 01 August 2020",
      "Repair plan formulated and discussed with BSEE on 22 September 2020",
      "Contractor hired to design, build, and test permanent sealing plug",
      "Motor Vessel mobilized on 14 October 2020 for subsea operations",
      "ROV operations conducted with tubing cutting tool",
      "Repairs completed and blind flange installed on 2 December 2020",
      "Well brought back into service on 2 December 2020"
    ],
    "summary": "On 27 June 2020 at 1725 hours, a subsea methanol leak was observed by an ROV operator on the Mississippi Canyon Block 503, Lease OCS-G 27277 SS002 subsea well (E1). The leak originated from the Methanol Injection Tree Valve (MITV) due to internal seal failure. Approximately 107 gallons of methanol was lost during diagnostic testing. The well was shut-in for scheduled maintenance when the leak was discovered. LLOG mobilized repair operations, and on 2 December 2020, after completing repairs, a blind flange was installed to isolate the leaking line and the well was returned to service.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Ensure quality assurance by the manufacture of subsea trees",
      "Isolate the MITV from all pressurized systems and produced fluids"
    ],
